[?2004l[?2004h> ## Issues Found
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. **Buffer not flushing**: save_checkpoint() didn't use context manager and didn't flush/fsync
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Result: Checkpoint file might not be written to disk before crash
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. **Semantic mismatch**: Saved batch_num as 'last_line' but used it to skip individual lines
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Example: If 5 batches processed (5000 records), checkpoint saved 5, resume only skipped 5 lines
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Result: Reprocessed almost everything from the beginning
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. **Data overwriting**: Used INSERT OR REPLACE instead of accumulating
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Result: On resume, previously aggregated data was replaced instead of accumulated
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 4. **No batch commits**: Only committed at the end
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Result: Data loss if crash occurred
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Fixes Applied
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. **save_checkpoint()**: Added context manager, flush(), and os.fsync()
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. **Line tracking**: Changed to track actual line numbers (i+1) instead of batch numbers
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. **SQL**: Changed to INSERT ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE to accumulate values
[?2004l[?2004h> 4. **Commits**: Added conn.commit() after each batch
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Test Results
